content.location: Second bolted route from the right.

climbs.name: Stinky Buddy
climbs.fa: Mike Bird, Greg M, Chris Powers, Gabe, DeAnna Caradine 7-18-07

content.description:
This is a bolted route that has adequate and safe natural gear placements from bottom to top  so pick your poison - bolts or gear.

As a gear route it is probably the best on this wall.  Start 4 feet to left of the bolts and boulder up a steep face, continue up the headwall (by passing the bolts and placing gear) to the anchors. Excellent gear protects the headwall moves to the top. Take a #1 and #2 BD-sized cams for these moves.

As a bolt route follow the bolts. Boulder the first part and continue up the headwall.
content.location: The sixth sport route from the left.

climbs.name: Skunk Buds
climbs.fa: Greg M, Aaron Weaver, Kate Russo 7-14-07

content.description: Climb up and over a small roof. Going left of the roof is the natural line but it is a bit harder going directly over it. Continue up a slab to the anchors.
content.location: Third bolted route from the left.

content.description: Steeper face within the blackened rock.

content.description: Climb a face up for 50'. The tends to the right at for the last 20'
content.location: Fourth bolted route from the left.

content.description: Climb a step face with single crack that splits into a Y that is squeezed in 10' to the right of Stinky Buddy.  Climb between the Y to the right side of the headwall that is part of Stinky Buddy. Surmount the head wall. Two cams in a horizontal crack protect the upper moves.
Squeezed in a few feet to the right of Stinky Stash is crack that leads up to a short left facing corner. From the top traverse right over to the anchors for Stinky Buddy.
content.location: Fifth gear route from the left.

content.description: Boulder up a short steepish face with a crack in it that is the start to GR #4. Move left to avoid the small step that is part of GR #4 and continue up the slab to the anchors that are part of Pepe LePue.
content.location: Fourth gear route from the left. Goes left after the first 15' of #8.

content.description:
Boulder up a short, steepish face with a crack in it that is squeezed in 10' to the right of Pepe LePue. After surmounting a small step it backs off. Continue up following the slightly vegetated crack, finally surmounting a steep step with a crack in at the top.

Stinky Stash now shares the last 15' (the steep step) with this route and as such has two bolts on it that were not part of the original ascent. There is adequate gear for competent gear leader so pick your poison. These two routes also share a common top anchor - however the anchors are on a fully detached block of rock. It is probably okay but one never knows.
content.location: Fourth gear route from the left.

content.description:
Climb a left-facing corner that is squeezed in just to the right of Skunk Buds. Skirt the roof by moving to the right. Climb the slab above to the anchors for Skunk Buds.

Note: Just above the roof is a nice 1/2" horizontal crack for pro.
content.location: Left facing corner that leads up to a roof, just to the right of SR #3.

content.description:
Climb the squeezed in crack line that is two feet to the right of Dog Farts and two feet to the left of Skunk Weed.

Surpisingly fun for a few moves if you stay out of the crack. Shares the anchors with Dog Farts.
content.location: First gear route from the left on the short wall.

content.description:
Climb the squeezed-in steep black face with a crack weakness in it that is three feet to the right Skunk Weed. Shares the anchors with Skunk Weed.

The lower bit of this can be wet from water seepage.
content.protection: A few small- to mid-sized cams.
content.location: Second gear route from the left.
